    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-01-31T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-01-31T10:00:00-05:00" n="759"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d759">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.515/944: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-31T16:00:00+01:00"
                            >January 31, 1944—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received January 31—12:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>846. Your 707 January 28 received this morning. I have already taken this matter
                    up with Mr. Eden<note n="74" xml:id="d759fn74">Anthony Eden, British Secretary
                        of State for Foreign Affairs.</note> and he has promised to act on it.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
